Of course, they can use roaming services with their own home SIM, in which case the Thai authorities will be short for them.
Operators of a country know only the relevant network information after crossing the border, i.e. after logging the SIM into their network.
So they know the phone number, but not the owner's information.
However, the difference in roaming prices from the rates of local operators is so dismal that even most tourists will start looking for local SIMs during their stay in Thailand.
The authorities’ efforts to monitor the movement of foreigners have received immediate criticism from foreigners residing in Thailand.
Tantasith calms the situation and compares the forthcoming system with the obligation to provide a residence address in immigration documents in connection with the protection of privacy.
In addition, the police will need a court order if they need to monitor a particular person.
